[00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.160]   This is a Kell blog post from August 24, 2005 titled "Square pegs and round holes."
[00:00:06.160 --> 00:00:10.400]   They say if your only tool is a hammer, then every problem looks like a nail.
[00:00:10.400 --> 00:00:15.120]   That's certainly a good way to think about how relational DBMS vendors have approached content.
[00:00:15.120 --> 00:00:18.080]   After all, if you're running a multi-billion dollar database business,
[00:00:18.080 --> 00:00:21.680]   then you are going to have two built-in biases when thinking about content.
[00:00:21.680 --> 00:00:26.080]   One, you will want to make content look like data, and two, you will assume the only thing
[00:00:26.080 --> 00:00:30.160]   people want to do with content is integrate it with content is integrate it with data.
